"The user browses View 1 at the [Overview] level and learns about the overall distribution of crop productivity metrics across districts and seasons. Next, the user selects a district or season of interest in View 1, and the filters propagate to View 2 and View 3 at the [Exploration] level where detailed distributions and correlations become visible. Then, the user explores yield trend predictions over time in View 4 at the [Insight] level, generating predictive models for specific districts and crops. Finally, the user identifies anomalies in productivity metrics across districts in View 5 at the [Detail] level for further investigation."